cs.DM, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with graph matching problem and its theoretical analysis in sparse Erdos-Renyi graphs. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper discusses the node-to-node correspondence between two correlated graphs. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the proposed algorithm assigns innovative features to high-degree nodes based on the tail of empirical degree distribution of their neighbor nodes. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper discusses the probability of having an edge between a pair of nodes in one of the graphs and also between the corresponding nodes in the other graph. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly mention the use of neural or evolutionary algorithms.
